@booboo: I noticed you used the term 'islamists'. What I don't understand is why the media in general uses that term. What those homicidal bastards really are are Muslims. So why the confusing term?

It's trendy words like islamists, journalists who are 'imbeded' (like a sliver), or using idiotic terms like 'phalangists (which can also refer to fingers) as opposed to phalanxes, and 'insurgents' when what they should say is what they mean: enemies.

Any thoughts? Anyone?

@thunderbum  -  What's confusing about it?  It is pretty clear what religion they follow and you knew what I who I was referring to.  Hell, once upon a time they were called Muhammedans and Moslems.  Some refer to politically active Muslims as Islamists but I honestly don't think it is that big of a deal.

It is good to call bullshit on the euphemisms, confusing terminology and PC nonsense but I really don't think the term is in the same league as the other words you mention.  Those terms are indeed absurd but it's not like I used a bullshit term like "overseas contingency operation" or "collateral damage". 

Honestly, man, there are battles that are worth the time and energy but I just don't think the word "Islamist" is one of them.

@booboo: you're right, of course in your explanation. It's just that sometimes smaller, aggravating points are like burrs under my saddle.

Yesterday I wasn't having one of my better days (idiots at work driving me nuts).

Cheers :)    (in a great mood today! )
